{{Infobox waterfall | name = Maniava | photo = Водоспад Манявський.jpg | photo_width = | photo_caption = | map = | map_width = | region = | source = | coords_ref = | location = [[Bohorodchanskyi Raion]], [[Ivano-Frankivsk Oblast]], [[Ukraine]] | type = | elevation = | height = {{convert|20|m|ft}} | height_longest = | number_drops = | width = | average_width = | watercourse = Maniavka (river) | average_flow = | world_rank = }}
'''Maniava waterfall''' ({{lang-uk|Манявський водоспад}}) is the highest [[waterfall]] in the [[Carpathians]] and is located in the [[Gorgany]] mountain ridge in [[Ukraine]].
==Geography== Maniava waterfall is located on the Maniavka river, about {{convert|8|km}} south of [[Maniava]], [[Bohorodchanskyi Raion]], [[Ivano-Frankivska oblast]].<ref name=carpathian>{{cite web|title=waterfalls - Ukrainian-Polish Tourist Portal|url=http://www.tourism-carpathian.com.ua/en/attractions/vodospady.php|publisher=tourism-carpathian.com|accessdate=1 February 2014}}</ref><ref name=carpathiansoutdoors>{{cite web|title=An easy Carpathian hike: castle, waterfalls, monastery. - Hiking ...|url=http://carpathiansoutdoors.com/en/tour/view/35|publisher=carpathiansoutdoors.com|accessdate=1 February 2014}}</ref>
It is nearly {{convert|20|m}} high. Near the waterfall is a canyon that is approximately {{convert|200|m}} long with rocks up to {{convert|20|m}} high.
==Overview== The waterfall also boasts a small lake, where the water remains cool even in hot season. Fir and beech forests line the waterfall creating a very beautiful and tranquil environment. The waterfall turns a little wild following heavy rainfall or the monsoon with frequent flash floods. In winter months frozen ice appear like chimeras with an enchanting effect on the visitors who frequent the place, now and again.<ref name=waterfall>{{cite web|title=Maniava Waterfall|url=http://rtic.if.ua/en/objects/c1/1243.html|publisher=rtic.if.ua|accessdate=1 February 2014}}</ref>
==See also== * [[Waterfalls of Ukraine]]
