{{Infobox protected area | name = Mrugavani National Park | alt_name = | iucn_category = II | photo = Pied Cuckoo (Clamator jacobinus) W IMG 9409.jpg | photo_width = | photo_alt = | photo_caption = [[Pied Cuckoo]] at Mrugavani National Park | map = India Telangana#India | map_width = | map_alt = | map_caption = Location in [[Telangana]], [[India]] | relief = | label = | label_position = | mark = | marker_size = | location = [[Chilkur, Ranga Reddy district|Chilkur]] near [[Hyderabad]], [[Telangana]] | nearest_city = [[Hyderabad]] | nearest_town = | coordinates = {{coord|17.355228|N|78.338159|E|format=dms|display=inline,title}} | coords_ref = | length = | length_mi = | length_km = | width = | width_mi = | width_km = | area = | area_ha = | area_acre = 1211 | area_km2 = | area_sqmi = | area_ref = | elevation = | elevation_avg = | elevation_min = | elevation_max = | dimensions = | designation = | authorized = | created = | designated = | established = | named_for = | visitation_num = | visitation_year = | visitation_ref = | governing_body = | administrator = | operator = | owner = | world_heritage_site = | website = | url = | child = | embedded = | embedded1 = | embedded2 = }}
'''Mrugavani National Park''' is a [[national park]] located in [[Hyderabad]], [[Telangana State]]. It is situated at [[Chilkur, Ranga Reddy district|Chilkur]] in [[Moinabad mandal]], 20&nbsp;km from [[Mahatma Gandhi Bus Station|MGBS]] and covers an area of {{convert|3.6|km2|sqmi}} or 1211 acres. It is home to a 600 different types of plant life. The Park is home to around 350 spotted deers. The animals include: [[indian hare]], [[forest cat]], [[civet]], [[Ptyas mucosus|Indian rat snake]], [[Daboia|Russell's viper]], [[cheetal]] and the [[flower pecker]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.telanganatourism.gov.in/partials/destinations/wildlife/hyderabad/mrugavani-national-park.html|title=Wild Life in Telangana :: Telangana Tourism|author=|date=|website=telanganatourism.gov.in|accessdate=18 April 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thehindu.com/life-and-style/homes-and-gardens/dear-how-about-some-deer-spotting/article22419685.ece|title=Dear, how about some deer spotting?|first=Prabalika M.|last=Borah|date=11 January 2018|publisher=|accessdate=18 April 2018|via=www.thehindu.com}}</ref>
==History== It was declared as a National Park in 1994.
==Flora== Teak, Bamboo, Sandal, Picus, Palas, Rela.
==Fauna== Cheetal, Sambar, Wild boar, Jungle Cat, Civet Cat, Mongoose Monitor Lizard, Python, Russell Viper, King Cobra
==Location== The Park is in near [[Chilkur Balaji Temple]], about 20&nbsp;km by road from [[Mahatma Gandhi Bus Station|MGBS]]
==See also== * [[Mahavir Harina Vanasthali National Park]] * [[Jawahar Deer Park]]
